{"questionId":"2535903","questionHtml":"<p>Find the possible values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> such that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>g</mi><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>k</mi></math> has exactly two solutions.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If final answer incorrect, award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for critical values <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn></math> seen anywhere.</p>\n<p>Exception to FT: <br>Award a maximum of <em><strong>A0A2FT</strong></em> if their graph from (a) is not symmetric about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2535903","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ1.8b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the possible values of k such that (g(x))2=k has exactly two solutions.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.16—Graphing modulus equations and inequalities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}